Now who&#39;s pretending that such occurrences are scarce? Do you think crime will just disappear if everyone has a gun? No. Desperate people will go to desperate lengths, which means evening the odds, which means getting guns of their own.

I don&#39;t know as much about Locke and Jefferson as I ought to, but I do not believe they held &quot;Don&#39;t bother me, I won&#39;t bother you&quot; as an absolute value.  They were probably more like &quot;You can bother me in some ways, but not in others, because we are a community after all, but after all I am an individual.&quot;
